1
00:01:09,468 --> 00:01:10,928
System...

2
00:01:10,928 --> 00:01:12,513
configuration,

3
00:01:12,513 --> 00:01:13,639
initializing.

4
00:01:14,348 --> 00:01:16,017
Final stage:

5
00:01:16,559 --> 00:01:18,185
Human emotions,

6
00:01:18,185 --> 00:01:19,604
facial recognition.

7
00:01:20,055 --> 00:01:21,055
Okay.

8
00:01:21,056 --> 00:01:22,056
Alright.

9
00:01:22,648 --> 00:01:23,858
Emotion number one...

10
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,391
[Laughing]

11
00:01:26,392 --> 00:01:27,560
Emotion detected.

12
00:01:27,903 --> 00:01:28,903
Happy.

13
00:01:29,780 --> 00:01:30,780
Check!

14
00:01:30,787 --> 00:01:31,807
Now, let's see.

15
00:01:31,809 --> 00:01:32,809
Do you know this?

16
00:01:34,668 --> 00:01:35,752
Emotion number two...

17
00:01:36,503 --> 00:01:43,385
[Crying]

18
00:01:43,988 --> 00:01:45,281
Emotion detected.

19
00:01:45,547 --> 00:01:46,547
Sad.

20
00:01:47,380 --> 00:01:48,466
Nice.

21
00:01:48,467 --> 00:01:49,635
Perfect!

22
00:01:51,261 --> 00:01:52,261
What else?

23
00:01:53,607 --> 00:01:54,805
Oh, I have something.

24
00:01:55,265 --> 00:01:56,933
Let's see if you'll get this.

25
00:01:57,934 --> 00:02:00,103
[Gagging]

26
00:02:00,507 --> 00:02:01,675
Disgust.

27
00:02:02,413 --> 00:02:03,581
Very good!

28
00:02:04,374 --> 00:02:05,583
Alright, last one.

29
00:02:09,754 --> 00:02:11,298
Let's see if you'll get this right.

30
00:02:11,714 --> 00:02:12,775
[Screaming]

31
00:02:12,780 --> 00:02:13,793
You have no shame.

32
00:02:14,367 --> 00:02:15,993
You're going to rot in hell!

33
00:02:16,577 --> 00:02:17,971
You think you did nothing wrong...

34
00:02:17,974 --> 00:02:20,286
but you did! You did! You did!

35
00:02:20,298 --> 00:02:21,966
- Angry.
- Wow!

36
00:02:22,675 --> 00:02:23,675
Nice.

37
00:02:23,968 --> 00:02:25,136
Perfect!

38
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:27,355
Alright, last one.

39
00:02:27,939 --> 00:02:29,524
Let's see if you can get this right.

40
00:02:30,066 --> 00:02:31,150
[Hysterical laugh]

41
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:35,506
[Crying]

42
00:02:35,512 --> 00:02:36,512
Crazy.

43
00:02:37,312 --> 00:02:38,855
Wow. Perfect!

44
00:02:39,258 --> 00:02:41,386
You're so ready.

45
00:02:41,771 --> 00:02:44,456
You're so good.

46
00:02:49,127 --> 00:02:51,484
Hi, my dream CEO.

47
00:02:51,491 --> 00:02:53,038
My ultimate crush.

48
00:02:53,045 --> 00:02:54,425
Emotion detected.

49
00:02:54,431 --> 00:02:55,431
Giddy.

50
00:02:58,583 --> 00:03:01,562
Hello? Who can resist him?

51
00:03:01,563 --> 00:03:02,856
Ernest Dimaguiba,

52
00:03:02,856 --> 00:03:04,536
The ultimate CEO.

53
00:03:04,543 --> 00:03:05,646
He's handsome...

54
00:03:05,652 --> 00:03:06,828
intelligent...

55
00:03:06,838 --> 00:03:07,838
rich.

56
00:03:07,839 --> 00:03:09,006
He has everything!

57
00:03:10,258 --> 00:03:11,733
I’m the only thing missing.

58
00:03:17,493 --> 00:03:18,867
I wonder how he's doing.

59
00:03:18,884 --> 00:03:20,867
I should be the one asking you that, Aiko.

60
00:03:20,871 --> 00:03:21,871
Oh.

61
00:03:21,884 --> 00:03:23,495
Engineer, you’re already here.

62
00:03:23,504 --> 00:03:25,220
- Have you been there for long?
- Uhuh.

63
00:03:25,957 --> 00:03:27,309
What's the status?

64
00:03:27,324 --> 00:03:28,443
How is the unit doing?

65
00:03:28,444 --> 00:03:29,803
Status is completed.

66
00:03:29,810 --> 00:03:32,879
She can recognize
all range of human emotions.

67
00:03:33,439 --> 00:03:35,208
I just tested her a while ago.

68
00:03:35,213 --> 00:03:37,215
But... of course, since

69
00:03:37,215 --> 00:03:38,550
she's a default system...

70
00:03:39,093 --> 00:03:41,226
she cannot change facial expressions.

71
00:03:41,233 --> 00:03:43,282
That's just how she is.
Just a pretty face. Like this.

72
00:03:43,288 --> 00:03:44,682
Great work!

73
00:03:44,688 --> 00:03:47,250
That’s the first
unit system ordered from us.

74
00:03:47,252 --> 00:03:49,647
So I'm sure Ernest
will be happy about this.

75
00:03:49,659 --> 00:03:52,339
- You mean, the Ernest Dimaguiba?
- Yep.

76
00:03:52,346 --> 00:03:55,156
Oh my gosh, he was the one
who ordered this unit?

77
00:03:55,156 --> 00:03:56,570
Emotion detected.

78
00:03:56,576 --> 00:03:57,904
Overreacting,

79
00:03:57,910 --> 00:03:58,910
excitement,

80
00:03:58,916 --> 00:04:00,323
in short... too extra.

81
00:04:01,476 --> 00:04:02,476
Recommendation:

82
00:04:02,481 --> 00:04:03,481
Needs sleep.

83
00:04:03,487 --> 00:04:04,487
She's right.

84
00:04:04,494 --> 00:04:05,679
But before you go to sleep...

85
00:04:05,687 --> 00:04:06,956
go and make me a cup of coffee.

86
00:04:06,967 --> 00:04:08,214
The one you make so well.

87
00:04:08,221 --> 00:04:09,221
Okay?

88
00:04:09,692 --> 00:04:10,692
Good night.

89
00:04:19,038 --> 00:04:20,766
So let me get this straight.

90
00:04:20,772 --> 00:04:22,833
They beat us to the deal again.

91
00:04:22,852 --> 00:04:26,165
Aren't we supposed to be the one
closing deals for promising inventions?

92
00:04:26,172 --> 00:04:27,172
Sir.

93
00:04:27,178 --> 00:04:28,688
Their roll-off was unexpected.

94
00:04:28,689 --> 00:04:31,129
Nothing is unexpected
if you're doing your job!

95
00:04:31,140 --> 00:04:32,826
Sir... We can adjust.

96
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:34,175
We don't adjust.

97
00:04:34,814 --> 00:04:36,148
We lead!

98
00:04:37,358 --> 00:04:39,068
Am I now supposed to do your job for you?

99
00:04:39,568 --> 00:04:40,903
What are you all even good for?

100
00:04:43,197 --> 00:04:44,197
Sir Ernest.

101
00:04:44,698 --> 00:04:46,158
Let's not burn the team.

102
00:04:47,138 --> 00:04:48,598
We can always recalibrate.

103
00:04:48,973 --> 00:04:50,055
It's one loss.

104
00:04:50,061 --> 00:04:51,061
We don't lose.

105
00:04:51,064 --> 00:04:53,810
I don't lose.

106
00:04:53,817 --> 00:04:55,360
I don't want to lose!

107
00:04:56,069 --> 00:04:57,755
I'm really tired, okay?

108
00:04:57,764 --> 00:04:58,882
Is that so hard to understand?

109
00:05:04,229 --> 00:05:05,229
Adjourned.

110
00:05:09,734 --> 00:05:11,152
Sir, here's your coffee.

111
00:05:19,609 --> 00:05:20,609
It's so...

112
00:05:20,616 --> 00:05:21,736
bitter!

113
00:05:21,742 --> 00:05:23,156
I'm sorry sir but maybe...

114
00:05:23,162 --> 00:05:24,162
Maybe what, Manang?

115
00:05:24,169 --> 00:05:26,396
You've been doing this for so long already.

116
00:05:26,402 --> 00:05:28,445
That's always been how I make it.

117
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:31,707
Oh, maybe I'm the...

118
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:35,293
I'm the one who forgot
and I'm the old one here.

119
00:05:35,294 --> 00:05:36,795
Me? Old?

120
00:05:36,796 --> 00:05:38,005
That's ridiculous, sir.

121
00:05:38,381 --> 00:05:39,382
[Crying]

122
00:05:40,424 --> 00:05:41,926
You're too sensitive, Manang.

123
00:05:43,219 --> 00:05:45,054
You better find someone else.

124
00:05:46,347 --> 00:05:47,598
Someone who doesn't have emotions...

125
00:05:48,099 --> 00:05:49,099
like you!

126
00:05:58,717 --> 00:06:01,261
Do you have something else to say?

127
00:06:02,017 --> 00:06:03,157
Sir?

128
00:06:03,165 --> 00:06:04,500
Aren't you going to...

129
00:06:04,896 --> 00:06:06,022
stop me from leaving?

130
00:06:06,814 --> 00:06:07,814
No.

131
00:06:08,758 --> 00:06:10,287
Finally!

132
00:06:10,299 --> 00:06:12,762
[Crying]

133
00:06:13,239 --> 00:06:17,502
[Crying]

134
00:06:27,613 --> 00:06:29,239
Hello Darwin, how's the unit?

135
00:06:30,580 --> 00:06:31,580
The robot?

136
00:06:32,206 --> 00:06:33,206
If it's ready?

137
00:06:33,694 --> 00:06:35,445
Hey... Is she ready?

138
00:06:38,415 --> 00:06:40,692
Of course! She's ready.

139
00:06:40,709 --> 00:06:41,960
Define...

140
00:06:42,544 --> 00:06:43,752
"ready."

141
00:06:43,752 --> 00:06:45,739
She's fully functional.

142
00:06:45,745 --> 00:06:48,324
I’ll bring it to you first thing tomorrow.

143
00:06:48,325 --> 00:06:50,631
So we can trial test her.

144
00:06:50,638 --> 00:06:51,638
Perfect.

145
00:06:51,645 --> 00:06:53,021
If the unit is good

146
00:06:53,021 --> 00:06:57,459
expect a huge amount of funds
for production and distribution.

147
00:06:57,465 --> 00:06:59,736
I won't fail you, my friend.

148
00:06:59,738 --> 00:07:01,379
I'll wait for the delivery tomorrow.

149
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:07,135
- Aiko.
- Yes?

150
00:07:07,145 --> 00:07:08,302
What's her status?

151
00:07:09,145 --> 00:07:10,145
Uh...

152
00:07:10,491 --> 00:07:11,760
What's happening to her?

153
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:13,058
I didn't do anything!

154
00:07:13,058 --> 00:07:15,036
Shut it down.
Shut it down now!

155
00:07:15,038 --> 00:07:16,038
Wait.

156
00:07:20,815 --> 00:07:21,815
Aiko!

157
00:07:21,822 --> 00:07:23,949
I can’t afford to embarrass myself
in front of Ernest.

158
00:07:24,670 --> 00:07:26,630
We’ll lose a big part of our funds.

159
00:07:27,283 --> 00:07:28,952
What will we bring tomorrow?

160
00:07:30,756 --> 00:07:32,202
We don't have anything to deliver.

161
00:07:48,564 --> 00:07:49,773
Ernest, my friend.

162
00:07:50,231 --> 00:07:52,233
It is with great pride
that I introduce to you...

163
00:07:54,057 --> 00:07:55,242
the future...

164
00:07:55,244 --> 00:07:56,637
of personal assistance.

165
00:08:12,428 --> 00:08:14,013
It's...

166
00:08:14,935 --> 00:08:16,353
I Love You...

167
00:08:16,788 --> 00:08:18,373
A-I-K-O.

168
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:20,959
Unit One.

169
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:24,087
Good morning, Boss Ernest.

170
00:08:24,586 --> 00:08:25,905
I am Aiko.

171
00:08:25,919 --> 00:08:27,172
Unit 0-1.

172
00:08:27,606 --> 00:08:28,899
Aiko for short.

173
00:08:29,252 --> 00:08:30,420
Nice to meet you.

174
00:08:32,499 --> 00:08:34,126
New place configured.

175
00:08:34,852 --> 00:08:36,525
Ready to be of service.

176
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:45,400
Oh my God, he’s even more
handsome in person.

177
00:08:45,401 --> 00:08:48,529
I think I’m about to faint, help!

178
00:08:58,384 --> 00:08:59,719
She looks...

179
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:01,480
different.

180
00:09:01,974 --> 00:09:05,478
This isn't what I saw from the
updates you sent me before.

181
00:09:06,229 --> 00:09:08,090
We made some adjustments.

182
00:09:08,106 --> 00:09:09,389
Refined features.

183
00:09:09,396 --> 00:09:10,396
The previous design looked better.

184
00:09:10,730 --> 00:09:12,823
Ouch, I’m not his type.

185
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:15,547
My friend, my friend.

186
00:09:15,550 --> 00:09:17,146
I guarantee you...

187
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:18,193
She's impressive

188
00:09:18,193 --> 00:09:20,236
and her performance is top-tier.

189
00:09:20,242 --> 00:09:22,815
Powered by advanced capabilities.

190
00:09:22,822 --> 00:09:26,095
She can handle easy to complex queries.

191
00:09:26,102 --> 00:09:27,102
Ask her something.

192
00:09:27,619 --> 00:09:28,870
Uhm...

193
00:09:30,659 --> 00:09:33,788
Initializing self-query demonstration.

194
00:09:34,413 --> 00:09:35,956
What is the weather today?

195
00:09:36,248 --> 00:09:38,954
Answer: It is partly cloudy.

196
00:09:38,959 --> 00:09:40,372
Chance of rain...

197
00:09:40,377 --> 00:09:41,545
Forty percent.

198
00:09:42,372 --> 00:09:44,415
See? She knows a lot!

199
00:09:44,813 --> 00:09:47,311
No matter what your
questions are, my friend.

200
00:09:47,319 --> 00:09:49,780
Even if it's about zodiac compatibilities.

201
00:09:50,906 --> 00:09:52,366
Uh... Not impressed.

202
00:09:52,366 --> 00:09:55,452
Those are all just...
basic information.

203
00:09:55,452 --> 00:09:56,787
Tell me, what more can she do?

204
00:09:57,899 --> 00:10:00,378
You don't have to charge or plug her in.

205
00:10:00,385 --> 00:10:01,678
She's solar powered.

206
00:10:02,312 --> 00:10:03,996
She doesn't eat or get hungry.

207
00:10:04,005 --> 00:10:05,005
She doesn't...

208
00:10:05,019 --> 00:10:06,020
use the bathroom.

209
00:10:08,033 --> 00:10:09,368
That's it?

210
00:10:09,953 --> 00:10:11,330
She can do so much more.

211
00:10:12,013 --> 00:10:13,515
I can do many other things.

212
00:10:13,785 --> 00:10:15,242
I'm very talented.

213
00:10:15,246 --> 00:10:16,616
You want me to sing?

214
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:18,038
Here is my sample performance:

215
00:10:18,539 --> 00:10:22,960
Do-re-mi-fa-so-la-ti-do!

216
00:10:23,460 --> 00:10:24,896
I can also dance.

217
00:10:24,909 --> 00:10:26,276
Here is my sample performance:

218
00:10:27,069 --> 00:10:28,069
Aiko, stop.

219
00:10:29,891 --> 00:10:30,892
Really, that's it?

220
00:10:31,448 --> 00:10:33,716
Of course, not.
She can do a lot more.

221
00:10:34,278 --> 00:10:35,696
Tell me, what more can you do?

222
00:10:36,036 --> 00:10:38,265
I can also do physical activities...

223
00:10:38,267 --> 00:10:39,434
like Karate.

224
00:10:40,060 --> 00:10:41,520
Sparring mate detected.

225
00:10:47,475 --> 00:10:48,852
[grunting]

226
00:10:49,548 --> 00:10:50,876
Aiko...

227
00:10:50,882 --> 00:10:51,883
That's enough.

228
00:10:56,248 --> 00:10:57,406
Just go and make me some coffee.

229
00:10:57,833 --> 00:10:59,001
Command acknowledged.

230
00:10:59,418 --> 00:11:00,502
Initiating.

231
00:11:01,525 --> 00:11:03,443
Alright, I'll just see if she's useful.

232
00:11:07,885 --> 00:11:09,970
What have I gotten myself into?

233
00:11:10,596 --> 00:11:12,639
I don’t think I can handle this.

234
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:15,508
Oh Aiko, you can do this.

235
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:18,261
For the sake of the money,
just don't back out.

236
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:19,888
Don't back out.

237
00:11:21,711 --> 00:11:23,004
Cut it out, Engineer.

238
00:11:23,641 --> 00:11:25,559
It looks like our friend is convinced.

239
00:11:26,328 --> 00:11:27,328
Well, go on.

240
00:11:27,334 --> 00:11:28,502
Make his coffee.

241
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:29,961
Make it good, okay?

242
00:11:30,670 --> 00:11:31,796
That's his first test.

243
00:11:32,547 --> 00:11:35,091
Engineer, making coffee
is nothing to me.

244
00:11:35,701 --> 00:11:38,328
What I can't do is this
deception we're doing.

245
00:11:38,328 --> 00:11:39,579
Don't you feel guilty?

246
00:11:40,107 --> 00:11:41,302
Because?

247
00:11:41,314 --> 00:11:43,036
Because he's my crush!

248
00:11:43,041 --> 00:11:45,983
How can I even keep it together?

249
00:11:45,992 --> 00:11:46,993
Whatever, Engineer.

250
00:11:47,493 --> 00:11:49,137
I almost fainted earlier,
just so you know.

251
00:11:49,146 --> 00:11:50,146
Wow.

252
00:11:50,532 --> 00:11:53,215
I was the one who almost fainted with your
gimmicks a while ago.

253
00:11:53,219 --> 00:11:54,219
I'm sorry, okay?

254
00:11:54,226 --> 00:11:56,676
You told me to step it up,
so I did, didn't I?

255
00:11:56,677 --> 00:11:58,655
Oh, didn't you also say that...

256
00:11:58,671 --> 00:11:59,672
you need this?

257
00:12:00,340 --> 00:12:00,798
Right?

258
00:12:00,924 --> 00:12:01,841
Engineer.

259
00:12:02,275 --> 00:12:03,651
Is it okay if...

260
00:12:04,432 --> 00:12:05,516
I can ask for an advance?

261
00:12:05,516 --> 00:12:07,936
I really need to send money to my mom.

262
00:12:07,936 --> 00:12:09,562
It's also an emergency.

263
00:12:09,569 --> 00:12:10,987
- I'll do anything.
- Anything?

264
00:12:10,987 --> 00:12:12,614
Yes, I really need it.

265
00:12:12,614 --> 00:12:13,775
Please, just this once.

266
00:12:13,781 --> 00:12:14,781
What...

267
00:12:14,785 --> 00:12:16,412
are you willing to do...

268
00:12:16,412 --> 00:12:18,164
for money?

269
00:12:19,025 --> 00:12:20,406
Oh, Engineer, please don't.

270
00:12:20,417 --> 00:12:23,629
I’ll do anything,
but I won’t sell my body.

271
00:12:23,629 --> 00:12:25,995
I'm not that kind of person.

272
00:12:26,004 --> 00:12:27,431
- No!
- Not even a chance.

273
00:12:27,437 --> 00:12:28,831
It's not like that!

274
00:12:28,843 --> 00:12:30,416
You misunderstood.

275
00:12:30,883 --> 00:12:32,009
You're not even my type.

276
00:12:32,551 --> 00:12:33,979
Oh.

277
00:12:34,003 --> 00:12:35,296
You're too harsh.

278
00:12:36,223 --> 00:12:39,267
So what exactly do you want me to do?

279
00:12:48,850 --> 00:12:49,850
Me?

280
00:12:50,477 --> 00:12:51,603
Robot.

281
00:12:51,936 --> 00:12:52,687
Robot--

282
00:12:52,687 --> 00:12:55,010
You're going to be his personal assistant.

283
00:12:55,010 --> 00:12:56,703
You’ll do everything that...

284
00:12:56,710 --> 00:12:59,028
needs to be done when he's there.

285
00:12:59,030 --> 00:13:00,163
Whenever he needs you.

286
00:13:00,531 --> 00:13:03,534
You can massage him...
Or even talk to him...

287
00:13:03,534 --> 00:13:05,849
- Massage him?
- Yes!

288
00:13:05,856 --> 00:13:08,609
What if he asks me to do
something and I don’t know how?

289
00:13:09,521 --> 00:13:10,521
You can do it.

290
00:13:10,534 --> 00:13:11,754
No!

291
00:13:11,761 --> 00:13:15,640
Never... Never! Never! Never!

292
00:13:15,641 --> 00:13:18,059
If only I didn't need the money.

293
00:13:18,834 --> 00:13:20,520
It's so tough being poor.

294
00:13:20,544 --> 00:13:22,504
This is just a one month trial test.

295
00:13:23,389 --> 00:13:24,950
While you're pretending to be a robot,

296
00:13:24,956 --> 00:13:27,140
I'll also be fixing the real unit.

297
00:13:27,166 --> 00:13:28,724
Then when it's good to go,

298
00:13:28,740 --> 00:13:30,029
I'll pull you out immediately.

299
00:13:30,033 --> 00:13:32,582
Then you can have your whole salary.

300
00:13:32,586 --> 00:13:33,849
What's important is...

301
00:13:33,853 --> 00:13:35,845
Ernest shouldn't find out about this.

302
00:13:35,859 --> 00:13:36,939
That's what I'm saying, Engineer.

303
00:13:36,940 --> 00:13:38,192
What if he finds out?

304
00:13:38,193 --> 00:13:40,836
What if I won't know the things
he'll ask me to do.

305
00:13:40,860 --> 00:13:42,087
What do I do?

306
00:13:42,111 --> 00:13:43,614
That smart watch you're wearing.

307
00:13:43,619 --> 00:13:44,619
Use it.

308
00:13:44,906 --> 00:13:46,032
You'll know everything.

309
00:13:46,032 --> 00:13:47,200
You won't mess up.

310
00:13:47,575 --> 00:13:48,575
I guess so.

311
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:50,888
Go on. Do it quickly!

312
00:13:50,893 --> 00:13:52,978
- Just go. We might get caught.
- Alright.

313
00:13:55,606 --> 00:13:56,606
Gosh.

314
00:14:05,293 --> 00:14:07,128
Here is your coffee, boss.

315
00:14:27,667 --> 00:14:28,993
Why does it taste like this?

316
00:14:38,246 --> 00:14:39,246
It's good!

317
00:14:39,580 --> 00:14:40,735
Very good, Aiko.

318
00:14:40,739 --> 00:14:41,739
It's like...

319
00:14:42,312 --> 00:14:44,341
it was made by a human.

320
00:14:44,839 --> 00:14:46,966
Thank you for the positive feedback, boss.

321
00:14:47,839 --> 00:14:50,717
Your satisfaction is my priority.

322
00:14:55,138 --> 00:14:56,598
Oh, I'm sorry.
I need to take this.

323
00:15:06,635 --> 00:15:07,970
Stay focused on your acting.

324
00:15:07,970 --> 00:15:08,970
Perfect, I hope.

325
00:15:09,688 --> 00:15:11,565
- Hey, stop being so giddy.
- What?

326
00:15:12,732 --> 00:15:15,836
What? You think I don't know
you have a crush on Ernest?

327
00:15:15,848 --> 00:15:16,848
Remember...

328
00:15:17,266 --> 00:15:18,476
No emotions.

329
00:15:19,219 --> 00:15:20,512
You're a robot, okay?

330
00:15:20,971 --> 00:15:22,055
Fine, okay?

331
00:15:23,006 --> 00:15:24,466
I'm sorry, Engineer.

332
00:15:25,036 --> 00:15:26,246
He's just so handsome.

333
00:15:26,617 --> 00:15:27,954
Can you blame me?

334
00:15:27,959 --> 00:15:29,085
For the last time...

335
00:15:29,419 --> 00:15:30,586
Don't ever forget

336
00:15:30,837 --> 00:15:32,505
the tasks you need to do.

337
00:15:32,831 --> 00:15:33,831
Copy.

338
00:15:33,851 --> 00:15:34,851
Well, go on. Be a robot.

339
00:15:39,178 --> 00:15:42,539
Ta-da! This is where
you'll self-charge or whatever,

340
00:15:42,550 --> 00:15:43,609
in this storage room.

341
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:46,750
Go.

342
00:15:47,073 --> 00:15:48,073
I'll leave you to it.

343
00:16:03,322 --> 00:16:04,573
Really, here?

344
00:16:06,883 --> 00:16:08,009
Am I not human?

345
00:16:10,910 --> 00:16:12,036
Right...

346
00:16:12,276 --> 00:16:14,069
I'm not supposed to act as a human.

347
00:16:14,403 --> 00:16:15,613
I'm a robot, aren't I?

348
00:16:17,865 --> 00:16:18,865
That's okay.

349
00:16:19,325 --> 00:16:20,493
It won't be like this forever.

350
00:16:21,029 --> 00:16:24,282
Your major role for the entire
day is a personal assistant.

351
00:16:24,533 --> 00:16:26,009
All of Ernest's meetings

352
00:16:26,016 --> 00:16:27,035
are held virtually.

353
00:16:27,035 --> 00:16:29,182
He doesn't take meetings in person.

354
00:16:29,196 --> 00:16:30,549
He only works at home.

355
00:16:30,562 --> 00:16:32,632
It has always been
his routine for two years.

356
00:16:32,642 --> 00:16:35,128
No more delays in reports.

357
00:16:35,136 --> 00:16:37,580
How many times
do I have to tell you this?

358
00:16:38,648 --> 00:16:41,567
I need updates constantly.

359
00:16:43,444 --> 00:16:44,444
You're dismissed.

360
00:16:45,958 --> 00:16:46,958
Wow.

361
00:16:47,272 --> 00:16:50,025
Even when he's angry,
he's still so handsome.

362
00:16:50,031 --> 00:16:51,031
Aiko.

363
00:16:51,291 --> 00:16:52,362
Did you take down everything?

364
00:16:52,365 --> 00:16:53,616
Yes, boss crush.

365
00:16:54,383 --> 00:16:55,410
What do you mean "crush"?

366
00:16:55,826 --> 00:16:56,953
Internet crashed.

367
00:16:58,079 --> 00:16:59,079
Fixing.

368
00:17:00,623 --> 00:17:01,832
System restored.

369
00:17:02,398 --> 00:17:03,780
Everything is noted, boss.

370
00:17:03,785 --> 00:17:04,785
Okay good.

371
00:17:04,792 --> 00:17:07,277
I also need a detailed summary
of the meeting earlier.

372
00:17:07,294 --> 00:17:08,294
Copy, boss.

373
00:17:12,383 --> 00:17:13,551
It's too early for it to...

374
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:15,570
"crash"?

375
00:17:15,589 --> 00:17:16,589
"Crash".

376
00:17:18,008 --> 00:17:19,008
"Crash".

377
00:17:19,016 --> 00:17:21,099
Control yourself, Aiko.

378
00:17:21,116 --> 00:17:24,036
Don’t make it obvious
or you’ll get caught.

379
00:17:24,741 --> 00:17:25,741
Don't cry.

380
00:17:26,641 --> 00:17:27,641
Don't cry...

381
00:17:30,414 --> 00:17:31,926
I really can't take it...

382
00:17:36,905 --> 00:17:37,948
How is the food preparation?

383
00:17:38,397 --> 00:17:41,853
Food preparation is at 38.97 percent.

384
00:17:47,234 --> 00:17:48,485
Are you malfunctioning?

385
00:17:51,405 --> 00:17:53,216
Is there liquid in your nose?
Colds?

386
00:17:53,221 --> 00:17:54,556
System error.

387
00:17:55,366 --> 00:17:56,533
Virus detected.

388
00:17:57,287 --> 00:17:59,431
The scent of onions

389
00:17:59,443 --> 00:18:00,443
can affect my system.

390
00:18:02,697 --> 00:18:04,657
Darwin failed to mention that to me.

391
00:18:05,497 --> 00:18:06,915
So those are dangerous for you?

392
00:18:10,842 --> 00:18:12,435
To be fair...

393
00:18:12,442 --> 00:18:13,551
he's actually kind of caring.

394
00:18:19,776 --> 00:18:20,776
[blows nose]

395
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:30,777
This robot is weird.

396
00:18:31,611 --> 00:18:33,112
System restored.

397
00:18:33,115 --> 00:18:34,922
Resuming cooking procedure.

398
00:18:35,375 --> 00:18:37,616
Forget that, just order me food online.

399
00:18:38,902 --> 00:18:40,589
Command acknowledged.

400
00:18:40,595 --> 00:18:41,846
Initiating...

401
00:18:41,846 --> 00:18:43,389
online food delivery.

402
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:52,774
And whenever you need to
do something as a human

403
00:18:52,781 --> 00:18:55,008
do it carefully and secretly.

404
00:18:55,021 --> 00:18:57,381
Never leave a trace behind.

405
00:18:59,128 --> 00:19:01,714
I’m already getting constipated
from holding it in.

406
00:19:03,674 --> 00:19:04,717
Aiko?

407
00:19:12,304 --> 00:19:13,347
Aiko?

408
00:19:17,217 --> 00:19:20,062
Yes, boss?
What can I do for you?

409
00:19:23,596 --> 00:19:25,164
[gagging]
What's that smell?

410
00:19:25,676 --> 00:19:27,803
It stinks so bad!

411
00:19:29,137 --> 00:19:30,389
Probable source:

412
00:19:31,290 --> 00:19:33,041
Drainage system or

413
00:19:33,041 --> 00:19:34,256
toilet bowl defect.

414
00:19:34,668 --> 00:19:36,146
Sanitation protocol:

415
00:19:36,150 --> 00:19:37,193
Cleaning required.

416
00:19:37,193 --> 00:19:39,529
Drainage?
That's from the drainage?

417
00:19:39,543 --> 00:19:41,062
It smells rotten!
It smells like...

418
00:19:41,063 --> 00:19:42,658
three days--
a dead rat--

419
00:19:42,663 --> 00:19:44,172
[gagging]

420
00:19:45,173 --> 00:19:47,550
It’s been a long time since
Manang last cleaned that.

421
00:19:48,246 --> 00:19:49,246
Just...

422
00:19:49,247 --> 00:19:50,356
Just...

423
00:19:50,372 --> 00:19:51,582
Just fix it okay?

424
00:19:53,092 --> 00:19:54,218
Acknowledged.

425
00:19:55,211 --> 00:19:56,629
Aren’t you done yet?

426
00:19:57,430 --> 00:19:58,639
Almost complete.

427
00:19:59,445 --> 00:20:00,655
Almost complete.

428
00:20:01,120 --> 00:20:02,120
Almost...

429
00:20:02,365 --> 00:20:05,034
Hold it in, don't sneeze please!

430
00:20:05,830 --> 00:20:06,830
[sneezing]

431
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:27,058
Ouch.

432
00:21:29,956 --> 00:21:31,833
May you both rest in peace.

433
00:21:35,586 --> 00:21:36,586
Aiko.

434
00:21:41,717 --> 00:21:45,513
Jesus Christ, I think I can die now.

435
00:21:45,972 --> 00:21:46,972
Aiko?

436
00:21:48,584 --> 00:21:49,701
Boss?

437
00:21:49,703 --> 00:21:51,705
Your medications are already prepared.

438
00:21:54,834 --> 00:21:55,834
Thank you.

439
00:21:57,378 --> 00:21:58,378
Warning.

440
00:21:58,948 --> 00:22:00,445
Exposure of injury

441
00:22:00,454 --> 00:22:02,373
to water is not advisable.

442
00:22:02,706 --> 00:22:04,708
Condition may worsen.

443
00:22:05,251 --> 00:22:08,076
Contacting the doctor
for medical evaluation.

444
00:22:09,191 --> 00:22:11,359
It’s just a minor injury,
it’ll be gone by tomorrow.

445
00:22:11,872 --> 00:22:12,914
Assessment...

446
00:22:13,206 --> 00:22:14,308
Not fine.

447
00:22:14,311 --> 00:22:15,855
Aiko, please.

448
00:22:17,857 --> 00:22:19,981
I don't want to talk to anyone.

449
00:22:19,989 --> 00:22:22,169
I don't want to go outside.
I don't want to see anyone.

450
00:22:22,176 --> 00:22:23,242
So don't bother.

451
00:22:23,616 --> 00:22:24,617
Copy, boss.

452
00:22:28,246 --> 00:22:29,414
Just help me put this on.

453
00:22:45,325 --> 00:22:46,325
[grunting]

454
00:22:57,055 --> 00:22:58,140
What are you doing?

455
00:22:58,724 --> 00:22:59,724
Uh..

456
00:23:00,475 --> 00:23:01,518
Apologies.

457
00:23:02,227 --> 00:23:03,812
Continuing assistance.

458
00:23:22,326 --> 00:23:23,326
Thank you.

459
00:23:24,124 --> 00:23:26,001
Is there anything else you need, boss?

460
00:23:26,368 --> 00:23:27,368
That's it.

461
00:23:27,374 --> 00:23:28,374
Copy, boss.

462
00:23:38,383 --> 00:23:39,676
Happy Birthday, Papa!

463
00:23:39,676 --> 00:23:41,553
- I love you, forever!
- Thank you, my dear!

464
00:23:41,553 --> 00:23:43,597
I love you too for ever and ever!

465
00:23:43,597 --> 00:23:45,341
I'm sure your mom loves you
so much too, right honey?

466
00:23:45,349 --> 00:23:47,968
Hon watch out, there's a bus!

467
00:23:52,689 --> 00:23:54,066
No.

468
00:23:59,154 --> 00:24:00,363
It's my fault.

469
00:24:00,363 --> 00:24:03,867
I couldn't save you, I'm sorry.

470
00:24:14,569 --> 00:24:15,946
Gosh, I'm so hungry.

471
00:24:17,030 --> 00:24:19,825
I’m going to get an ulcer from this.

472
00:24:20,575 --> 00:24:21,910
That's what you get.

473
00:24:30,335 --> 00:24:31,335
Aiko?

474
00:24:33,463 --> 00:24:35,424
Boss detected.

475
00:24:39,386 --> 00:24:40,512
What are you doing?

476
00:24:41,263 --> 00:24:42,597
You're eating?

477
00:24:43,316 --> 00:24:44,574
Reminder:

478
00:24:44,588 --> 00:24:45,588
You should not...

479
00:24:46,026 --> 00:24:47,402
waste food.

480
00:24:47,408 --> 00:24:48,493
You should not?

481
00:24:48,910 --> 00:24:49,952
You should not

482
00:24:49,952 --> 00:24:51,240
waste food.

483
00:24:54,874 --> 00:24:57,418
Wait, so if you're eating human food...

484
00:24:58,180 --> 00:24:59,598
how are you able to digest?

485
00:24:59,598 --> 00:25:00,891
Are you that advanced?

486
00:25:03,352 --> 00:25:04,413
Error.

487
00:25:04,419 --> 00:25:05,605
Error.

488
00:25:05,619 --> 00:25:07,092
System malfunction.

489
00:25:07,613 --> 00:25:08,864
Recalibrating.

490
00:25:09,206 --> 00:25:10,458
Recalibrating.

491
00:25:13,305 --> 00:25:14,848
System restored.

492
00:25:16,046 --> 00:25:17,088
It seems that...

493
00:25:17,679 --> 00:25:18,930
you've been glitching way too often.

494
00:25:18,930 --> 00:25:20,603
I may need to call Darwin.

495
00:25:22,934 --> 00:25:23,934
Query:

496
00:25:24,144 --> 00:25:25,437
Why are you still awake, boss?

497
00:25:29,066 --> 00:25:31,109
I just woke up and
I can't go back to sleep.

498
00:25:31,109 --> 00:25:32,444
I feel like having coffee.

499
00:25:32,944 --> 00:25:33,945
Can you make me one?

500
00:25:34,488 --> 00:25:35,488
Acknowledged.

501
00:25:35,864 --> 00:25:37,365
Preparing coffee.

502
00:25:40,118 --> 00:25:41,453
I'll just be outside.

503
00:25:45,829 --> 00:25:46,919
Here, boss.

504
00:25:46,922 --> 00:25:48,049
Thank you, Aiko.

505
00:25:48,727 --> 00:25:50,521
Do you need something else, boss?

506
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:53,793
If there's nothing else,
I'll go ahead to recharge.

507
00:25:58,069 --> 00:26:01,072
Can you stay here for a while
and keep me company, please?

508
00:26:07,533 --> 00:26:08,992
Emotion detected.

509
00:26:09,660 --> 00:26:10,911
Sad.

510
00:26:12,788 --> 00:26:13,788
You're right.

511
00:26:16,762 --> 00:26:18,764
Safe space mode on.

512
00:26:19,419 --> 00:26:21,088
Feel free to talk now.

513
00:26:21,878 --> 00:26:23,588
I'm here to listen.

514
00:26:25,509 --> 00:26:27,177
You can trust me, boss.

515
00:26:27,511 --> 00:26:30,222
I can secure confidential information.

516
00:26:31,223 --> 00:26:33,433
Nobody else will ever know.

517
00:26:36,186 --> 00:26:38,522
I keep dreaming about the accident.

518
00:26:42,633 --> 00:26:45,053
The day I lost my wife and daughter.

519
00:26:49,408 --> 00:26:52,202
The day I couldn’t do
anything to save them.

520
00:26:55,828 --> 00:26:57,622
Even now, I still can't accept it.

521
00:27:00,252 --> 00:27:02,296
After that tragedy, it's like...

522
00:27:04,339 --> 00:27:05,924
It's like I've changed.

523
00:27:06,633 --> 00:27:08,760
Everything became too
heavy for me to bear.

524
00:27:09,924 --> 00:27:12,927
I became emotionally unstable.

525
00:27:13,406 --> 00:27:16,993
I started terrorizing everyone around me,

526
00:27:20,647 --> 00:27:23,275
I thought it would be best
to isolate myself...

527
00:27:24,276 --> 00:27:26,486
to lock myself up in this house.

528
00:27:28,270 --> 00:27:29,939
So, I also thought to...

529
00:27:30,903 --> 00:27:32,738
try you out because you're a robot.

530
00:27:34,912 --> 00:27:36,538
No emotions.

531
00:27:38,165 --> 00:27:39,958
I can't hurt you, or...

532
00:27:41,418 --> 00:27:43,378
you won't get affected by my emotions.

533
00:27:44,588 --> 00:27:45,839
Assessment:

534
00:27:46,298 --> 00:27:48,091
Your decision is valid.

535
00:27:48,993 --> 00:27:49,993
Boss.

536
00:27:50,552 --> 00:27:52,471
As part of my services...

537
00:27:53,055 --> 00:27:56,433
I'll help you regain
your emotional stability.

538
00:28:06,109 --> 00:28:07,109
How?

539
00:28:08,202 --> 00:28:09,453
Trust me.

540
00:28:17,643 --> 00:28:20,107
Therapeutic sessions will begin today.

541
00:28:20,110 --> 00:28:21,110
Are you ready?

542
00:28:21,561 --> 00:28:22,604
- Yes.
- Inhale.

543
00:28:23,939 --> 00:28:25,065
Exhale-- Ha!

544
00:28:25,351 --> 00:28:26,351
Ha!

545
00:28:26,363 --> 00:28:27,363
Inhale.

546
00:28:29,152 --> 00:28:30,403
Exhale. Ha!

547
00:28:30,419 --> 00:28:31,419
Ha!

548
00:28:32,113 --> 00:28:34,324
Inhale...

549
00:28:34,532 --> 00:28:35,992
[humming]

550
00:28:36,187 --> 00:28:38,022
Exhale.

551
00:28:41,790 --> 00:28:42,832
Inhale.

552
00:28:44,584 --> 00:28:45,669
Exhale.

553
00:28:48,296 --> 00:28:50,590
Our therapeutic session has ended.

554
00:28:53,468 --> 00:28:55,220
Congratulations, boss.

555
00:28:56,388 --> 00:28:58,265
Sir, here are the latest numbers.

556
00:29:16,866 --> 00:29:17,866
Uh, boss.

557
00:29:18,159 --> 00:29:19,159
Stress ball...

558
00:29:19,369 --> 00:29:20,369
to calm yourself.

559
00:29:20,578 --> 00:29:22,706
You need to control your emotions.

560
00:29:27,335 --> 00:29:28,335
Okay.

561
00:29:28,503 --> 00:29:30,088
Let's review that again.

562
00:29:30,338 --> 00:29:32,299
I think we can still improve the numbers.

563
00:29:32,299 --> 00:29:33,383
Let's focus on...

564
00:29:33,883 --> 00:29:34,883
strategy.

565
00:29:35,427 --> 00:29:36,427
Not only on the outside.

566
00:29:37,470 --> 00:29:40,432
Positive behavioral adjustment detected.

567
00:29:40,432 --> 00:29:41,474
Good job, boss.

568
00:29:42,771 --> 00:29:44,523
Next slide, please.

569
00:29:45,061 --> 00:29:46,122
Boss...

570
00:29:46,130 --> 00:29:47,131
just a reminder.

571
00:29:47,896 --> 00:29:50,149
Some fruits, like apples,

572
00:29:50,149 --> 00:29:52,109
help support complete nutrition.

